ion**\nSince our assumption that **r3c5** is shaded leads to a violation of the rules, we must conclude that **r3c5** cannot be shaded.  \nTherefore, **r3c5** must remain unshaded.\n\n---\n\nThis step-by-step process ensures that all Hitori rules are followed and helps us determine the correct state of cell **r3c5**.",
